studyDesigns.name: Study Design
studyDesigns.rationale: Protocol-defined study design for investigating efficacy and safety

arms.name: Treatment Arm A (Placebo + BR)
arms.description: Placebo capsules administered orally once daily continuously in combination with bendamustine and rituximab (BR) for 6 cycles, followed by rituximab maintenance for responders.

arms.name: Treatment Arm B (Ibrutinib + BR)
arms.description: Ibrutinib 560 mg administered orally once daily continuously in combination with bendamustine and rituximab (BR) for 6 cycles, followed by rituximab maintenance for responders.

population.name: Study Population
population.description: Target population defined by eligibility criteria

objectives.name: Primary Objective
objectives.text: To evaluate whether the addition of ibrutinib to bendamustine and rituximab will result in prolongation of progression-free survival (PFS) in subjects with newly diagnosed MCL who are 65 years of age or older.

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - ORR
objectives.text: Evaluation of overall response rate (CR+ partial response [PR])

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Patient-Reported Symptoms
objectives.text: Evaluation of patient-reported lymphoma symptoms and concerns as measured by the lymphoma (Lym) subscale of the Functional Assessment of Cancer Therapy-Lymphoma (FACT-Lym)

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - MRD
objectives.text: Evaluation of minimal residual disease (MRD) negative rate

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Safety
objectives.text: Evaluation of safety of ibrutinib when combined with BR

objectives.name: Secondary Objective - Pharmacokinetics
objectives.text: To characterize the pharmacokinetics of ibrutinib and explore the potential relationships between ibrutinib metrics of exposure with relevant clinical, pharmacodynamic, or biomarker information

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective - PRO
objectives.text: To evaluate patient-reported outcomes (PRO) related to well-being and general health status utilizing the FACT-Lym and EuroQol (EQ-5D-5L)

objectives.name: Exploratory Objective - Biomarkers
objectives.text: To explore biomarkers identified from other studies of ibrutinib in samples collected for MRD assessments

endpoints.name: Primary Efficacy Endpoint
endpoints.text: Progression-free survival (PFS) as determined by investigators

endpoints.name: FACT-Lym Subscale
endpoints.text: Lymphoma (Lym) subscale of the Functional Assessment of Cancer Therapy-Lymphoma (FACT-Lym)

endpoints.name: Safety Endpoints
endpoints.text: Safety assessed by physical examinations, ECOG criteria, laboratory tests, monitoring adverse events, and concomitant medication usage

endpoints.name: Pharmacokinetic Parameters
endpoints.text: Model-derived plasma concentrations or metrics of exposure parameters (eg, maximum observed plasma concentration [Cmax] or area under the plasma concentration versus time curve [AUC])

endpoints.name: Exploratory PRO
endpoints.text: Patient-reported outcomes (PRO) related to well-being and general health status utilizing the FACT-Lym and EuroQol (EQ-5D-5L)

endpoints.name: Exploratory Biomarkers
endpoints.text: Biomarkers identified from other studies of ibrutinib in samples collected for MRD assessments

analysisPopulations.name: Intent-to-Treat Population
analysisPopulations.text: The ITT population includes all subjects who are randomized. This population will be used for the primary efficacy analysis and all other efficacy analyses, unless otherwise specified.
analysisPopulations.label: ITT
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The ITT population includes all subjects who are randomized. This population will be used for the primary efficacy analysis and all other efficacy analyses, unless otherwise specified.

analysisPopulations.name: Safety Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The Safety Analysis Set includes all randomized subjects who received at least one dose of any study treatment (ibrutinib/placebo, bendamustine, or rituximab).
analysisPopulations.label: SAF
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The Safety Analysis Set includes all randomized subjects who received at least one dose of any study treatment (ibrutinib/placebo, bendamustine, or rituximab).
analysisPopulations.criteria: Randomized AND received >=1 dose of any study treatment

analysisPopulations.name: Per-Protocol Set
analysisPopulations.text: The per-protocol set is a subset of the ITT population, excluding subjects with major protocol deviations that may impact the primary efficacy endpoint. The specific criteria for exclusion will be finalized prior to database lock.
analysisPopulations.label: PP
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The per-protocol set is a subset of the ITT population, excluding subjects with major protocol deviations that may impact the primary efficacy endpoint. The specific criteria for exclusion will be finalized prior to database lock.
analysisPopulations.criteria: ITT population AND no major protocol deviations

analysisPopulations.name: PK Analysis Set
analysisPopulations.text: The PK analysis set includes all subjects who received at least one dose of ibrutinib and have at least one evaluable PK sample.
analysisPopulations.label: PK
analysisPopulations.populationDescription: The PK analysis set includes all subjects who received at least one dose of ibrutinib and have at least one evaluable PK sample.
analysisPopulations.criteria: Received >=1 dose of ibrutinib AND >=1 evaluable PK sample

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Age requirement
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Subject is 65 years of age or older

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: MCL Diagnosis
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Diagnosis of MCL must include morphology and expression of either cyclin D1 in association with other relevant markers (eg, CD19, CD20, PAX5, CD5) or evidence of t(11;14) as assessed by cytogenetics, fluorescent in situ hybridization (FISH), or polymerase chain reaction (PCR)

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Disease Stage
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Stage II, III, or IV disease by Ann Arbor Classification

eligibilityCriterionItems.name: Measurable Disease
eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Must have at least 1 measurable site of disease

eligibilityCriterionItems.text: Avoid co-administration with strong or moderate CYP3A inhibitors and consider alternative agents with less CYP3A inhibition

studyInterventions.name: Ibrutinib
studyInterventions.description: First-in-class, potent, orally-administered, covalently-binding small molecule inhibitor of Brutons tyrosine kinase (BTK).

studyInterventions.name: Bendamustine hydrochloride
studyInterventions.description: Antineoplastic alkylating agent used in combination with rituximab (BR regimen).

studyInterventions.name: Rituximab
studyInterventions.description: CD20-directed cytolytic antibody used in induction and maintenance phases.

studyInterventions.name: Antimicrobial prophylaxis
studyInterventions.description: Permitted and should be considered for subjects at increased risk for opportunistic infections.

studyInterventions.name: Anti-hormonal therapy
studyInterventions.description: Permitted after discussion with the sponsors medical monitor.

studyInterventions.name: Warfarin
studyInterventions.description: Prohibited; other vitamin K antagonists are also prohibited.

studyInterventions.name: Fish oil and Vitamin E
studyInterventions.description: Supplements that should be avoided due to bleeding risk.

studyInterventions.name: Strong or moderate CYP3A inhibitors
studyInterventions.description: Should be avoided; if required, ibrutinib dose must be reduced or withheld.

amendments.name: Amendment INT-7
amendments.summary: To update safety information to align with the ibrutinib Investigators Brochure (IB) to include information regarding cerebrovascular accidents as a new safety observation identified from the post-marketing setting, and to clarify that assessment of pulse/heart rate and blood pressure is expected at every protocol-specified visit until end of treatment.

amendments.name: Amendment INT-4
amendments.summary: The knowledge gained on the efficacy of ibrutinib from completed randomized clinical studies, which was not available at time of MCL3002 study design, and the lower than expected event rate are the key drivers for this amendment. The sponsor has added a second interim analysis to occur at approximately 180 PFS events to mitigate for the potential long interval between the planned first interim analysis (134 PFS events) and the final analysis (265 PFS events).

amendments.name: Amendment INT-3
amendments.summary: To update the safety language for diarrhea and other safety topics in the Introduction, the background safety information for ibrutinib has been aligned with the recently updated ibrutinib Investigators Brochure (IB) and other protocols within the clinical development program.

commentAnnotations.text: Janssen Research & Development is a global organization that operates through different legal entities in various countries.
Vital sign assessments should be recorded in source documents but will not be routinely collected in the eCRF.
Maximal tumor reduction defined as time of CR or when 2 consecutive CT scans show no further tumor reduction.
For subjects with an increased risk of tumor lysis syndrome (TLS) or other toxicities, rituximab can be split over a 2-day period.
If a dose of study drug is not taken at the scheduled time, it can be taken as soon as possible on the same day.

studyDefinitionDocumentVersions.description: Update safety information regarding cerebrovascular accidents and clarify vital sign monitoring.
Halt collection of CR MRD samples except for new CR assessments.
Clarify DMC recommendations and update hepatic impairment dose modifications.
Addition of a second interim analysis at 180 PFS events.
Initial release of the clinical protocol.

studyAmendmentImpacts.description: Updated safety information to include cerebrovascular accidents as a new safety observation from post-marketing settings.
Added mandatory pulse/heart rate and blood pressure monitoring at every protocol-specified visit.
Added specific dose modification instructions for subjects with chronic hepatic impairment based on Child-Pugh classification.
Broadened the definition of major hemorrhagic events to include any Grade 3+ event or CNS hemorrhage.

studyAmendmentReasons.reasonText: To update safety information to align with the ibrutinib Investigators Brochure (IB) regarding cerebrovascular accidents.
To halt the collection of complete response (CR) minimal residual disease (MRD) samples for subjects already having an MRD-negative sample.
Addition of a second interim analysis to mitigate for the potential long interval between the first interim and final analysis.
Minor editorial changes implemented to correct typographical errors and address inconsistencies.
